Class Sociocast

java.lang.Object

All Implemented Interfaces:
SociocastAPI
public class Sociocast
extends java.lang.Object
implements SociocastAPI

Core class for interacting with the Sociocast API.

Call newInstance(Context context, String apikey, String secret, String clid, boolean sandbox) with your main application activity and your Sociocast apikey, secret, client id. Additionally @param sandbox should be set to true when testing and false when you want to push data to the live environment.

Once you have an instance, you can call general Sociocast API methods.

The Sociocast library will periodically send information to Sociocast servers, so your application will need to have android.permission.INTERNET.

There is also general documentation available at sociocast.com
